# NIX BUILD
Nixpkgs: nixpkgs.nix
Source: https://github.com/NixOS/nix
Description: Build a Nix derivation.
Version: nix --version

## Commands

### Basics
- nix build nixpkgs#hello: Build the 'hello' package.

### Essentials
- nix build .: Build the default package of the local flake.
- nix build .#my-package: Build a specific attribute.

### Intermediaries
- nix build --print-out-paths nixpkgs#htop: Show the resulting /nix/store path.
- nix build --no-link .: Build without creating the 'result' symlink.

### Advanceds
- nix build --rebuild .: Force a rebuild even if the result is in the store.

### Uncommons
- nix build --dry-run .: See what would be built/downloaded.

## Tips
- Resulting binaries are usually found in the './result' folder.

## Disclaimers
- Building large packages from source can take hours.

## Alternatives
- nix-build (legacy): Standard build tool before flakes.

